	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Ah, yes. Replace the S-CPU with the 10.5MHz SA-1, but keep the HDMA. With I-RAM you can access in one cycle at that rate, and automatic bitmap-&gt;bitplane DMA transformation, software scaling would be trivial.
<br />
<br />Sadly, none of the SA-1 games really took advantage of the power of that chip.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


