	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />As I understand it, SA-1 was supposed to be in the Super NES CD-ROM system cartridge. But when Nintendo dismissed each of its partners, they switched to an instruction set that had more of a future. Philips made CD-i (all toasters toast toast!) with a customized 68000-based CPU, while Sony used MIPS for the PlayStation.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

